788
00:32:16,940 --> 00:32:17,980
 And if you're going to call me to be single,

789
00:32:17,980 --> 00:32:19,540
 you're not going to give me anybody to marry.

790
00:32:19,540 --> 00:32:20,820
 Then I guess this is the only way that I'm going to be able

791
00:32:20,820 --> 00:32:22,980
 to process these sort of emotions.

792
00:32:22,980 --> 00:32:23,820
 Maybe it's not that.

793
00:32:23,820 --> 00:32:25,980
 Maybe it's God, I'm not hurting my witness.

794
00:32:25,980 --> 00:32:26,840
 Like it's not that big of a deal.

795
00:32:26,840 --> 00:32:29,780
 I'm not hurting my witness if everybody around me is saved.

796
00:32:29,780 --> 00:32:32,180
 Oh my gosh.

797
00:32:32,180 --> 00:32:38,460
 We justify our sin,

798
00:32:38,460 --> 00:32:43,700
 our indulgences and our addiction all the time

799
00:32:43,700 --> 00:32:50,520
 simply because it feels good to do bad things.

800
00:32:50,520 --> 00:32:53,940
 You know what God has to say about that?

801
00:32:55,420 --> 00:32:59,860
 He says in Galatians 6, "Do not be deceived.

802
00:32:59,860 --> 00:33:01,860
 I'm not mocked.

803
00:33:01,860 --> 00:33:07,080
 For whatever one sows, that will he also reap.

804
00:33:07,080 --> 00:33:08,800
 For the one who sows his own flesh

805
00:33:08,800 --> 00:33:10,420
 will from the flesh reap corruption,

806
00:33:10,420 --> 00:33:12,160
 but the one who sows to the spirit

807
00:33:12,160 --> 00:33:14,800
 will from the spirit reap eternal life."

808
00:33:14,800 --> 00:33:17,560
 What's that passage saying?

809
00:33:17,560 --> 00:33:21,600
 It's saying you cultivate whatever you tolerate.

810
00:33:21,600 --> 00:33:24,640
 You cultivate whatever you tolerate.

811
00:33:24,640 --> 00:33:26,920
 So like whatever sin it is you're tolerating,

812
00:33:26,920 --> 00:33:30,420
 that is the sin that you're cultivating.

813
00:33:30,420 --> 00:33:32,980
 So what are you tolerating?

814
00:33:32,980 --> 00:33:35,820
 Maybe it seems harmless right now,

815
00:33:35,820 --> 00:33:38,480
 but I guarantee you it will not be harmless later on.

816
00:33:38,480 --> 00:33:41,160
 I remember talking to a friend of mine.

817
00:33:41,160 --> 00:33:43,240
 It was right after I made the switch from college ministry

818
00:33:43,240 --> 00:33:44,280
 into young adult ministry.

819
00:33:44,280 --> 00:33:46,720
 And he said something that really stuck with me.

820
00:33:46,720 --> 00:33:47,800
 It resonated to this day.

821
00:33:47,800 --> 00:33:50,280
 He was like, "Dude, young adult ministry is awesome.

822
00:33:50,280 --> 00:33:51,120
 You're going to love it.

823
00:33:51,120 --> 00:33:52,540
 It's amazing.

824
00:33:52,540 --> 00:33:55,460
 But there's something you need to be aware of.

825
00:33:55,460 --> 00:33:59,120
 In college ministry, you see the seeds of sin.

826
00:33:59,120 --> 00:34:04,200
 But in young adult ministry, you see the fruit of sin."

827
00:34:04,200 --> 00:34:05,140
 Why is that?

828
00:34:05,140 --> 00:34:09,340
 Because if sin goes untamed,

829
00:34:09,340 --> 00:34:13,360
 sin runs wild.

830
00:34:13,360 --> 00:34:18,320
 It must be addressed,

831
00:34:18,320 --> 00:34:20,400
 which is why I am pleading with you tonight

832
00:34:20,400 --> 00:34:22,200
 to do something about it.

833
00:34:22,200 --> 00:34:25,760
 Like I am begging you, don't just justify the struggle,

834
00:34:25,760 --> 00:34:30,600
 mortify the struggle, put it to death, put it down.

835
00:34:30,600 --> 00:34:32,440
 Nothing likes to die in this life.

836
00:34:32,440 --> 00:34:34,720
 Your sin doesn't either.

837
00:34:34,720 --> 00:34:38,120
 And yet I'm praying you would do something about it.

838
00:34:38,120 --> 00:34:39,680
 Gosh, I'm praying you would do something about it.

839
00:34:39,680 --> 00:34:40,680
 I'm running out of time,

840
00:34:40,680 --> 00:34:43,760
 but I just feel the need to keep pushing into you

841
00:34:43,760 --> 00:34:46,980
 to not just indulge a bunch of religious activity,

842
00:34:46,980 --> 00:34:51,980
 but to literally lean into the spiritual reality

843
00:34:52,180 --> 00:34:54,740
 that you have an enemy.

844
00:34:54,740 --> 00:34:56,780
 He doesn't want you to do well.

845
00:34:56,780 --> 00:34:58,860
 He doesn't want you to experience life.

846
00:34:58,860 --> 00:35:00,860
 He doesn't want you to find joy.

847
00:35:00,860 --> 00:35:02,820
 And so he will bait you, lure you,

848
00:35:02,820 --> 00:35:05,540
 take you into other places, promising you

849
00:35:05,540 --> 00:35:07,380
 you'll find it there, when in reality,

850
00:35:07,380 --> 00:35:09,220
 he knows it's not over there at all.

851
00:35:09,220 --> 00:35:13,200
 Do something about it.

852
00:35:13,200 --> 00:35:16,380
 Confess your sin.

853
00:35:16,380 --> 00:35:18,500
 Get some friends.

854
00:35:18,500 --> 00:35:20,060
 Wage war.

855
00:35:20,060 --> 00:35:22,380
 Strengthen your weak knees.

856
00:35:22,380 --> 00:35:24,180
 Like go to battle against that

857
00:35:24,180 --> 00:35:26,180
 which is going to battle against you.

858
00:35:26,180 --> 00:35:30,340
 Because you're already promised the victory.

859
00:35:30,340 --> 00:35:33,360
 You already know death is defeated.

860
00:35:33,360 --> 00:35:37,820
 So why then would you fear?

861
00:35:37,820 --> 00:35:43,300
 Go to work, kill that which is seeking to kill you.

862
00:35:43,300 --> 00:35:44,740
 And you don't have to do it alone.

863
00:35:44,740 --> 00:35:47,000
 David tells us that you get to do it alongside friends,

864
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:48,720
 which is where he goes in verse five.

865
00:35:48,720 --> 00:35:51,100
 He says, "Let a righteous man strike me.

866
00:35:51,100 --> 00:35:52,320
 "It's a kindness.

867
00:35:52,320 --> 00:35:53,440
 "Let him rebuke me.

868
00:35:53,440 --> 00:35:54,820
 "It's oil for my head.

869
00:35:54,820 --> 00:35:56,780
 "Let my head not refuse it."

870
00:35:56,780 --> 00:36:00,900
 The third step David gives us for controlling our cravings

871
00:36:00,900 --> 00:36:03,400
 is you have to find friends who will correct you.

872
00:36:03,400 --> 00:36:07,140
 You have to find friends who will correct you.

873
00:36:07,140 --> 00:36:08,460
 He tells us two really important things

874
00:36:08,460 --> 00:36:10,100
 about combating our cravings in this passage.

875
00:36:10,100 --> 00:36:11,520
 He tells us, number one,

876
00:36:11,520 --> 00:36:13,580
 you've got to find righteous friends.

877
00:36:13,580 --> 00:36:16,180
 And number two, they need to interact with you

878
00:36:16,180 --> 00:36:18,540
 in a righteous sort of way.

879
00:36:18,540 --> 00:36:19,940
 When he says that they need to be righteous,

880
00:36:19,940 --> 00:36:20,820
 what does that mean?

881
00:36:20,820 --> 00:36:25,340
 A righteousness in the Bible is equivalent to godliness,

882
00:36:25,340 --> 00:36:26,980
 which we talk about a lot today.

883
00:36:26,980 --> 00:36:30,000
 So it isn't just someone that claims to know God.

884
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:33,060
 It's someone that is seeking to become like him.

885
00:36:33,060 --> 00:36:35,780
 That doesn't just say they've been saved by Jesus,

886
00:36:35,780 --> 00:36:37,960
 but is seeking to become like him.

887
00:36:37,960 --> 00:36:38,960
 That's what you're looking for.

888
00:36:38,960 --> 00:36:40,300
 You're looking for someone

889
00:36:40,300 --> 00:36:43,860
 that is serious about pursuing holiness.

890
00:36:43,860 --> 00:36:45,260
 Why do you want to find that?

891
00:36:45,260 --> 00:36:47,500
 Someone that wants to be separate from their sin.

892
00:36:47,500 --> 00:36:48,820
 Because if they're so serious

893
00:36:48,820 --> 00:36:50,300
 about being separate from their sin,

894
00:36:50,300 --> 00:36:51,380
 they're probably going to be helpful

895
00:36:51,380 --> 00:36:53,340
 to helping you separate yourself from your own.

896
00:36:53,340 --> 00:36:54,220
 That makes sense.

897
00:36:54,220 --> 00:36:57,820
 When I showed up to Dallas, I did not have a barber.

898
00:36:57,820 --> 00:37:00,140
 I desperately needed to find someone to cut my hair.

899
00:37:00,140 --> 00:37:01,380
 And so what did I do?

900
00:37:01,380 --> 00:37:03,660
 I looked across all the land

901
00:37:03,660 --> 00:37:06,700
 for the best head of hair I could find.

902
00:37:06,700 --> 00:37:09,220
 And when I found it, I asked that gentleman,

903
00:37:09,220 --> 00:37:10,900
 where'd you get your haircut?

904
00:37:10,900 --> 00:37:12,300
 And he told me where he got his haircut.

905
00:37:12,300 --> 00:37:14,220
 And that's now where I get my haircut to this day.

906
00:37:14,220 --> 00:37:15,900
 Why did I do that?

907
00:37:15,900 --> 00:37:20,180
 Because there were signs of credibility in his life.

908
00:37:20,180 --> 00:37:23,900
 And thus, I gave him dignity to speak into mine.

909
00:37:23,900 --> 00:37:25,180
 Makes sense how that works.

910
00:37:25,180 --> 00:37:26,540
 We do this in every area of life.

911
00:37:26,540 --> 00:37:28,220
 You want to get fit, you look to someone that's fit.

912
00:37:28,220 --> 00:37:29,800
 You want to get healthy, you look to someone that's healthy.

913
00:37:29,800 --> 00:37:31,380
 You want to get smart, you look to someone that's smart.

914
00:37:31,380 --> 00:37:34,060
 This is the way that we learn in life.

915
00:37:34,060 --> 00:37:36,380
 If you want to combat your sin,

916
00:37:36,380 --> 00:37:37,340
 you're going to need people

917
00:37:37,340 --> 00:37:39,580
 that are serious about doing that themselves.

918
00:37:39,580 --> 00:37:42,420
 He also tells us how we should interact.

919
00:37:42,420 --> 00:37:44,300
 He tells us that we should interact in a way

920
00:37:44,300 --> 00:37:46,380
 that's characterized by two different words.

921
00:37:46,380 --> 00:37:49,580
 The first is, he says they should strike him,

922
00:37:49,580 --> 00:37:51,780
 which is a little off-putting.

923
00:37:51,780 --> 00:37:52,780
 Can we just admit that?

924
00:37:52,780 --> 00:37:54,700
 I don't know that I necessarily want a friend to strike me

925
00:37:54,700 --> 00:37:57,180
 until you understand what the Hebrew means.

926
00:37:57,180 --> 00:38:00,100
 The Hebrew tells us that it's the idea

927
00:38:00,100 --> 00:38:03,500
 of someone speaking with decisive impact.

928
00:38:03,500 --> 00:38:06,080
 So it would be the idea of when they speak,

929
00:38:06,080 --> 00:38:07,680
 it's like they swing the hammer,

930
00:38:07,680 --> 00:38:10,320
 and thus they deal the blow.

931
00:38:10,320 --> 00:38:11,220
 That's what you want.

932
00:38:11,220 --> 00:38:13,380
 You want someone that when they speak,

933
00:38:13,380 --> 00:38:15,820
 it makes a material difference in your life.

934
00:38:15,820 --> 00:38:17,220
 That's not the only thing though.

935
00:38:17,220 --> 00:38:19,500
 He says that he wants someone who will rebuke him,

936
00:38:19,500 --> 00:38:21,540
 meaning someone that will gently admonish him

937
00:38:21,540 --> 00:38:22,380
 or correct him.

938
00:38:22,380 --> 00:38:25,920
 You want someone that can do both of these things.

939
00:38:25,920 --> 00:38:28,780
 You see, you want people in your life

940
00:38:28,780 --> 00:38:30,740
 who love you enough to tell you the things

941
00:38:30,740 --> 00:38:31,820
 that you need to hear,

942
00:38:31,820 --> 00:38:33,960
 not the things that you want to hear.

943
00:38:33,960 --> 00:38:38,060
 In the Bible, it authenticates this kind of friendship.

944
00:38:38,060 --> 00:38:40,260
 A few verses, just so you can take my word for it.

945
00:38:40,260 --> 00:38:41,260
 Proverbs 27, six says,

946
00:38:41,260 --> 00:38:45,060
 "Faithful or trusted are the wounds of a friend,

947
00:38:45,060 --> 00:38:47,620
 but profuse are the kisses of an enemy."

948
00:38:47,620 --> 00:38:49,940
 Proverbs 28, 23, "Whoever rebukes a man

949
00:38:49,940 --> 00:38:51,380
 will afterward find more favor

950
00:38:51,380 --> 00:38:53,320
 than he who flatters with his tongue."

951
00:38:53,320 --> 00:38:55,540
 And then Jesus even said this in Revelation 3, 19,

952
00:38:55,540 --> 00:38:56,560
 at the end of all time, he said,

953
00:38:56,560 --> 00:39:00,780
 "Those whom I love, I reprove and I discipline."

954
00:39:00,780 --> 00:39:02,660
 Isn't that interesting that that's what he says there?

955
00:39:02,660 --> 00:39:04,460
 "I reprove them, I discipline them.

956
00:39:04,460 --> 00:39:08,100
 I love them, so be zealous and repent."

957
00:39:08,100 --> 00:39:09,420
 I know these types of friendships

958
00:39:09,420 --> 00:39:11,660
 have been some of the greatest gifts in my life.

959
00:39:11,660 --> 00:39:14,980
 Like whenever I've been in seasons of particular hardship

960
00:39:14,980 --> 00:39:18,720
 and thus struggle, my friends and I have come together

961
00:39:18,720 --> 00:39:21,500
 and we have literally written questions

962
00:39:21,500 --> 00:39:23,600
 we want the others to ask us.

963
00:39:23,600 --> 00:39:25,620
 Why do we do that?

964
00:39:25,620 --> 00:39:30,460
 Because nobody knows me better than me, minus my wife.

965
00:39:30,460 --> 00:39:32,460
 But I know myself really well.

966
00:39:32,460 --> 00:39:35,500
 I know where I go whenever I'm tempted.

967
00:39:35,500 --> 00:39:38,260
 I know what I do whenever I'm bored.

968
00:39:38,260 --> 00:39:42,220
 I know when I'm tired, what is my inclination?

969
00:39:42,220 --> 00:39:44,100
 Like I know myself.

970
00:39:44,100 --> 00:39:46,460
 And so rather than someone trying to ask me questions

971
00:39:46,460 --> 00:39:48,540
 and investigate what's going on,

972
00:39:48,540 --> 00:39:51,740
 what if I just handed them the appropriate list of questions

973
00:39:51,740 --> 00:39:54,020
 to interrogate me thoroughly?

974
00:39:54,020 --> 00:39:56,380
 That would be the wisest thing for me to do.

975
00:39:56,380 --> 00:39:58,780
 That would be the wisest thing for all of us to do,

976
00:39:58,780 --> 00:40:02,000
 to look to a friend that is again, godly, man.

977
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:05,060
 They are serious about pursuing Jesus

978
00:40:05,060 --> 00:40:08,500
 and they're willing to speak honestly with you.

979
00:40:08,500 --> 00:40:11,980
 And so you give them the set of questions

980
00:40:11,980 --> 00:40:14,920
 and you let them investigate your life.

981
00:40:14,920 --> 00:40:17,620
 You have some risky conversations

982
00:40:17,620 --> 00:40:19,940
 that are gonna leave you exposed.

983
00:40:19,940 --> 00:40:22,460
 Does it feel good to be exposed?

984
00:40:22,460 --> 00:40:27,180
 No, but it is better to be exposed with a friend

985
00:40:27,180 --> 00:40:29,420
 than safe in your sin.

986
00:40:29,420 --> 00:40:32,420
 So you find someone who wants to get into the thick

987
00:40:32,420 --> 00:40:33,340
 of it with you.

988
00:40:34,180 --> 00:40:39,180
 You find the godliest friends you can.

989
00:40:39,180 --> 00:40:44,020
 You hand them a list of questions

990
00:40:44,020 --> 00:40:47,900
 and you give them permission to ask you all of them

991
00:40:47,900 --> 00:40:49,300
 at least once a week.

992
00:40:49,300 --> 00:40:52,360
 It'll be what David says.

993
00:40:52,360 --> 00:40:54,420
 It'll be the kindest thing they can do to you.

994
00:40:54,420 --> 00:40:55,780
 It'll be like oil on your head.

995
00:40:55,780 --> 00:40:59,400
 It'll be honoring to you for them to do these things.

996
00:40:59,400 --> 00:41:00,980
 Okay, last thing, let's keep going.

997
00:41:00,980 --> 00:41:02,180
 Verses eight through 10.

998
00:41:03,020 --> 00:41:07,580
 David says, "But my eyes are toward you, oh God, my Lord.

999
00:41:07,580 --> 00:41:09,580
 In you I seek refuge.

1000
00:41:09,580 --> 00:41:11,820
 Leave me not defenseless.

1001
00:41:11,820 --> 00:41:14,940
 Keep me from the trap that they've laid for me,

1002
00:41:14,940 --> 00:41:17,340
 from the snares of evil doers.

1003
00:41:17,340 --> 00:41:20,180
 Let the wicked fall into their own nets

1004
00:41:20,180 --> 00:41:21,820
 while I pass by safely."

1005
00:41:21,820 --> 00:41:26,980
 The fourth and final step to controlling your cravings

1006
00:41:26,980 --> 00:41:30,500
 is you have to pursue intimacy with God.

1007
00:41:32,140 --> 00:41:34,100
 You have to pursue intimacy with God.

1008
00:41:34,100 --> 00:41:36,300
 By the end of this Psalm,

1009
00:41:36,300 --> 00:41:42,020
 David's circumstances are not changed.

1010
00:41:42,020 --> 00:41:45,580
 Like he's not magically or miraculously pulled

1011
00:41:45,580 --> 00:41:47,900
 out of all the hardship that he's facing.

1012
00:41:47,900 --> 00:41:51,340
 Instead, he is still in the midst of it.

1013
00:41:51,340 --> 00:41:53,380
 But rather than be where he was at the beginning,

1014
00:41:53,380 --> 00:41:55,620
 distracted by what everybody was doing,

1015
00:41:55,620 --> 00:41:58,760
 he's a laser focused on what God is doing.

1016
00:41:58,760 --> 00:42:00,780
 He has set his gaze.

1017
00:42:00,780 --> 00:42:05,140
 I love the way it says, "My eyes are toward you, oh God.

1018
00:42:05,140 --> 00:42:08,360
 In you I seek refuge."

1019
00:42:08,360 --> 00:42:15,780
 If you walk into a room and you see that what you want,

1020
00:42:15,780 --> 00:42:19,660
 you don't aimlessly move around.

1021
00:42:19,660 --> 00:42:22,740
 You're filled with purpose.

1022
00:42:22,740 --> 00:42:25,620
 And so you pursue wholeheartedly.

1023
00:42:25,620 --> 00:42:27,100
 That's what he's saying.

1024
00:42:27,100 --> 00:42:30,260
 Get your eyes on God.

1025
00:42:30,260 --> 00:42:31,780
 And as you do so,

1026
00:42:31,780 --> 00:42:36,100
 he'll take care of all the traps

1027
00:42:36,100 --> 00:42:39,260
 and all the snares and all the nets.

1028
00:42:39,260 --> 00:42:41,740
 What does it look like to get your eyes on God?

1029
00:42:41,740 --> 00:42:44,060
 I love the way that Thomas Chalmers,

1030
00:42:44,060 --> 00:42:47,660
 who wrote "The Expulsive Power of New Affection."

1031
00:42:47,660 --> 00:42:49,500
 He says this, he says,

1032
00:42:49,500 --> 00:42:52,180
 "The best way to overcome the world

1033
00:42:52,180 --> 00:42:54,180
 is not with morality and self-discipline.

1034
00:42:54,180 --> 00:42:55,580
 Pull yourself up by your bootstraps."

1035
00:42:55,580 --> 00:42:56,620
 No.

1036
00:42:56,620 --> 00:43:00,820
 Christians overcome the world by seeing the beauty

1037
00:43:00,820 --> 00:43:03,380
 and the excellence of Christ.

1038
00:43:03,380 --> 00:43:05,380
 They overcome the world

1039
00:43:05,380 --> 00:43:08,700
 by seeing something more attractive than the world.

1040
00:43:08,700 --> 00:43:16,140
 So how do you see he who is most attractive of all?

1041
00:43:16,140 --> 00:43:20,380
 How do you set your eyes and fix your gaze

1042
00:43:20,380 --> 00:43:21,780
 to behold his beauty?

1043
00:43:21,780 --> 00:43:24,180
 I'll give you two ideas very quickly.

1044
00:43:24,180 --> 00:43:29,180
 Number one is you avoid unnecessary temptation.

1045
00:43:29,180 --> 00:43:30,900
 You avoid unnecessary temptation.

1046
00:43:30,900 --> 00:43:32,140
 James 1:14 tells us,

1047
00:43:32,140 --> 00:43:33,860
 "But each person is tempted

1048
